# AlarmNet360 API Getting Started Guide

Welcome to the AlarmNet360 API Getting Started Guide. This guide provides comprehensive steps for onboarding accounts and utilizing APIs within AlarmNet360.

## Introduction

Before you start using AlarmNet360 APIs, it is mandatory for customers to obtain API permission. To ensure a smooth and compliant integration, please follow the steps below: 

- Create an account at [https://developer.honeywellhome.com](https://developer.honeywellhome.com/), and agree to the API Terms of Service agreement.  

- After creating your account, navigate to the “My Apps” section and select “Create New App”: 
  
  ![](data:image/png;base64,) ![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Provide the App Name and Callback URL to get the token to complete the sign-in and data sharing process: 
  
  ![](data:image/png;base64,)
  
  *Note: For a guide on the callback URL and data sharing process, please follow the steps on this guide: [OAuth2 Guide](https://developer.honeywellhome.com/content/oauth2-guide).*

- Upon app creation, you will get your Customer key and Customer secret. Either the Customer key or the App Name must be provided to Resideo: 
  
  <img src="data:image/png;base64," title="" alt="" width="319">

## Account Onboarding

There are four primary flows for account creation, **PRO Series Panel** will be used as an example on the following account onboarding explanation below:

1. **Security-only account creation.**
   
   To create a Security-only account, the following mandatory customer information is required: 
   
   - Customer Information: Type of Customer (Residential or Commercial). 
   
   - Location Details: Name, Subscriber Id, Address, Country, and Zip code. 
   
   - Panel Information: MAC and CRC. 
   
   Once you have all the required information, proceed to make the following request to create the account:
   
   - **Endpoint:** Send a **POST** request to *'https://api.honeywellhome.com/AlarmNet360API/v1.2/Locations'* 
   
   - **Example Request Body:** Include the following parameters in the request body:
     
     ```
     {
         "Customer": {
             "CustomerType": "Residential"
         },
         "Location": {
             "Name": "ProPlusLocation",
             "SubscriberId": "99-6C-9999",
             "InstallationAddress": {
                 "Country": "USA",
                 "Zip": "11747"
             }
         },
         "Panel": {
             "Communicator": [
                 {
                     "MAC": "B82CA0BE36CE",
                     "CRC": "210C"
                 }
             ]
         }
      }
     ```
   
   - **Result:** Account creation will be completed with provided parameters. You will have to use the registration API to activate the account, refer to the "Account Activation" section for more information.

2. **Security account with Total Connect.**
   
   To create a Security account with Total Connect, the following mandatory customer information is required:
   
   - Customer Information: Customer Type (Residential or Commercial). 
   
   - Location Details: Name, Subscriber Id, Address, Country, and Zip code. 
   
   - Panel Communicator Information: MAC and CRC. 
   
   - Total Connect Information: Account Name, Master Username, Panel User Code, and Email ID. 
   
   - Additionally, select either 'SmartHome' or 'SmartSecurity' for the Billing Package.
   
   Once you have all the required information, proceed to send the following request to create the account:
   
   - **Endpoint:** Send a **POST** request to *'https://api.honeywellhome.com/AlarmNet360API/v1.2/Locations'*
   
   - **Example Request Body:** Include the following parameters in the request body:
     
     ```
     {
         "Customer": {
             "CustomerType": "Residential"
         },
         "Location": {
             "Name": "ProPlusLocation",
             "SubscriberId": "99-6C-9999",
             "InstallationAddress": {
                 "Country": "USA",
                 "Zip": "11747"
             },
             "SelectedPackageDetails": {
                 "Packagetype": "SmartHome"
             }
         },
         "Panel": {
             "Communicator": [
                 {
                     "MAC": "B82CA0BE36CE",
                     "CRC": "210C"
                 }
             ]
         },
         "TotalConnectLocation": {
             "AccountName": "JohnDoeTCAccount",
             "MasterUser": {
                 "Name": "ProMacUser",
                 "Code": "4567",
                 "EmailId": "AN3601@gmail.com"
             }
         }
      }
     ```
   
   - **Result:** Account creation will be completed with provided parameters. You will have to use the registration API to activate the account, refer to the "Account Activation" section for more information.

3. **Linking a new Total Connect account to an existing security account.**
   
   To link an existing Security account with a new Total Connect account, you will need to set the *'LinkExistingTCAccount'* flag to *'false'*.
   
   - **Endpoint:** Send a **POST** request to *'https://api.honeywellhome.com/AlarmNet360API/v1.2/Locations'*
   
   - **Example Request Body:** Include the following parameters in the request body:
     
     ```
     {
         "Customer": {
             "CustomerType": "Residential"
         },
         "Location": {
             "Name": "ProPlusLocation",
             "SubscriberId": "99-6C-9999",
             "InstallationAddress": {
                 "Country": "USA",
                 "Zip": "11747"
             },
             "SelectedPackageDetails": {
                 "Packagetype": "SmartHome"
             }
         },
         "Panel": {
             "Communicator": [
                 {
                     "MAC": "B82CA0BE36CE",
                     "CRC": "210C"
                 }
             ]
         },
         "TotalConnectLocation": {
             "AccountName": "JohnDoeTCAccount",
             "MasterUser": {
                 "Name": "ProMacUser",
                 "Code": "4567",
                 "EmailId": "AN3601@gmail.com"
             },
             "LinkExistingTCAccount": false
         }
     }
     ```
   
   - **Result:** Linking will be completed.

4. **Linking existing security and Total Connect accounts.**
   
   To link an existing Security account with an existing Total Connect account, you will need to set the *'LinkExistingTCAccount'* flag to *'true'*.
   
   - **Endpoint:** Send a **POST** request to *'https://api.honeywellhome.com/AlarmNet360API/v1.2/Locations'*
   
   - **Example Request Body:** Include the following parameters in the request body:
     
     ```
     {
         "Customer": {
             "CustomerType": "Residential"
         },
         "Location": {
             "Name": "ProPlusLocation",
             "SubscriberId": "99-6C-9999",
             "InstallationAddress": {
                 "Country": "USA",
                 "Zip": "11747"
             },
             "SelectedPackageDetails": {
                 "Packagetype": "SmartHome"
             }
         },
         "Panel": {
             "Communicator": [
                 {
                     "MAC": "B82CA0BE36CE",
                     "CRC": "210C"
                 }
             ]
         },
         "TotalConnectLocation": {
             "AccountName": "JohnDoeTCAccount",
             "MasterUser": {
                 "Name": "ProMacUser",
                 "Code": "4567",
                 "EmailId": "AN3601@gmail.com"
             },
             "LinkExistingTCAccount": true
         }
     }
     ```
   
   - **Result:** Linking will be completed.

## Account Types and Variants.

For **Lynx** and **Vista** panel types, additional mandatory panel information is required to create an account: 

- Panel ID 

- Panel Template 

- Panel Revision 

- Panel Name

To gather the necessary information for these panel types, follow the outlined steps below:

1. **Obtaining Panel ID and Panel Name:**
   
   - **Process:** Send a GET request to the following endpoint: *'https://api.honeywellhome.com/AlarmNet360API/v1.2/PanelTypes'*
   
   - **Result:** The response will list various Panel IDs and Names. Select the ID and Name corresponding to your specific panel type.

2. Obtaining Panel Revision: 
   
   - **Process:** Send a GET request to the following endpoint: *'https://api.honeywellhome.com/AlarmNet360API/v1.2/PanelRevisions?panelId={PanelID}'*
     
     *Note: Replace {PanelID} with the actual Panel ID obtained in the previous step.*
   
   - **Result:** The server will respond with the relevant Panel Revision for your specific Panel ID.

3. Obtaining Panel Template: 
   
   - **Process:** Send a GET request to the following endpoint: *'https://api.honeywellhome.com/AlarmNet360API/v1.2/panelId={{PanelID}}&panelRevisionId={{PanelRevisionID}}&countryCode=USA'*
     
     *Note: Replace {PanelID} and {PanelRevisionID} with the appropriate Panel ID and Revision information previously obtained.*
   
   - **Result:** The response will provide the Panel Template necessary for account creation.

Once you have collected all the required information (Panel ID, Template, Revision, and Name), you are ready to proceed with creating the account. Follow the standard account creation process, incorporating this specific panel information.

## What can you do with AlarmNet360 APIs?

Here are some general points on what you can do with AlarmNet360 APIs: 

- User Management: The APIs allow for the creation, deletion, and management of user accounts. 

- Accessing Historical Data: The APIs can be used to access historical data for analysis. This can include data on panel changes, or access logs. 

- Device Management: You can manage and configure individual devices within the panel, including cameras, keyfobs, sensors, and alarms.

## Example API Calls

### Getting a list of all users for a panel:

Make sure you have an OAuth2 token before making a request. Follow the OAuth2 steps in [this guide](https://developer.honeywellhome.com/content/oauth2-guide) on how to get a token.

- **Request:**
  
  ```
  curl --location 'https://api.honeywellhome.com/AlarmNet360API/v1.2/panels/{deviceId}/users' 
  
  --header 'Authorization: bearer {token}' 
  ```

- **Response Snippet:** You will receive a 200 HTTP status code response if any user is registered on the provided panel:
  
  ```
  [
      {
          "id": 1,
          "name": "Installer",
          "code": "4112",
          "hasDoorLockAccess": false,
          "partitionAccessList": [
              {
                  "partitionNumber": 1,
                  "authorityLevel": "Installer"
              }
          ]
      }
  ]
  ```

### Add a Keypad to a panel:

Make sure you have an OAuth2 token before making a request. Follow the OAuth2 steps in [this guide](https://developer.honeywellhome.com/content/oauth2-guide) on how to get a token.

- **Request:**
  
  ```
  curl --location 'https://api.honeywellhome.come/AlarmNet360API/V1.2/panels/{deviceId}/keypads' 
  --header 'Authorization: bearer {token}' 
  --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \ 
  --data '{ 
      "SerialText": "8ACBA4FFFE26BF79", 
      "Type": "Rf6", 
      "Configuration": { 
          "PartitionId": 1, 
          "ZoneId": 850, 
          "Description1": "Test", 
          "Description2": "Keypad", 
          "ConnectionMode": "Rf6", 
          "SupervisionInterval": 0 
      }, 
      "Status": { 
          "State": "Guru", 
          "IsEnrolled": false, 
          "LastUpdatedUTC": "2023-09-26T11:33:43.528Z" 
      } 
  }' 
  ```

- **Response Snippet:** You will receive a 200 HTTP status code response if any user is registered on the provided panel:
  
  ```
  { 
      "serialText": "8ACBA4FFFE26BF79", 
      "type": "Rf6", 
      "version": { 
          "software": ":", 
          "hardware": ":" 
      }, 
      "configuration": { 
          "partitionId": 1, 
          "zoneId": 850, 
          "description1": "Test", 
          "description2": "Keypad", 
          "connectionMode": "Rf6", 
          "shortAddress": "0", 
          "supervisionInterval": 60 
      }, 
      "status": { 
          "state": "NotEnrolled", 
          "lastUpdatedUTC": "0001-01-01T00:00:00" 
      } 
  } 
  ```
